\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that the programme meets minimum requirements for all the relevant criteria and recommended that the programme be accredited.\line \line The programme supports the institutional strategic objectives with a strong focus on developing leadership skills in community and civic organisations.  The Institution provided a budget for the development of e-classrooms and learning materials for the eight modules of the programme.  This supports the notion that students need to accept more responsibility for their own learning.  The programme further aims to strengthen a culture of research and innovation by allocating a total of 28 credits in two modules.  The programme purpose and outcomes are at the appropriate NQF level 8.  \line \line The described horizontal and vertical articulation pathways are appropriate.  The programme design allocates sufficient time for the learning activities which are well described.  The institutional policy on the development of learning programmes provides guidance for the development of learning materials.\line \line The programme targets those that are in full-time employment or in their own business.  Student admission is granted to those applicants who have completed an Advanced Diploma in Tourism Management\'2C the student admission requirements are aligned with statutory requirements.  Access is widened through RPL under the guidance of the institutional RPL Policy.  The department where the programme will be offered uses a ranking system where student admission is granted to students scoring best\'2C taking designated groups into account.  The Enrolment Plan provides for a realistic first cohort of 20 students then growing to 30 students in four years.  \line \line As this is a public Institution\'2C Criteria 3\'2C 4\'2C 7 and 8 are deemed to be in place.\line \line The Institution follows a student-centered approach promoting active student learning.  The teaching approach is suitable for a programme pitched at NQF level 8 programme and a range of appropriate teaching approaches will be utilised.  The selection of teaching and learning activities are suitable for the demands and nature of the programme.  Students will be exposed to assisted e-leaning technologies to manage their own learning.  Each student will be allocated a supervisor who will guide them to complete a Research Project.  \line \line An orientation session will inform students regarding the availability of student support and programme demands.  Learning material will be available on the learning material.  Student progress will be monitored and support provided to at-risk students.  Mentors will be used to provide further guidance to students.  \line \line The Institution has an Assessment Policy in place which guides assessment practice.  A range of assessment types are used to enhance student learning including provision of formative feedback to students.  Provision is made for both internal and external moderation.  Students have the opportunity to provide feedback on their learning experience providing lecturers the opportunity to reflect and adapt their teaching and assessment practices.  \line \line The Directorate notes that the Institution has included a Research Methods and Design\'E2\'80\'99 module as well as an \'E2\'80\'98Applied Business Project\'E2\'80\'99 module in the programme along with learning outcomes linked to research.  It is also mentioned in section 5.2 of the submission that the research- based modules will develop the ability of students to conduct independent studies\'2C gather information independently\'2C and to communicate the findings of their independent endeavours. It is further mentioned that - each student will be allocated a supervisor\'2C who will provide the requisite guidance to enable the student to complete a research report. In terms of the \'E2\'80\'9CApplied Business Project\'E2\'80\'9D module\'2C the supervisor will continuously reassess the module\'2C until he\'2Fshe is satisfied that the Research Report is of an acceptable standard to be submitted for external moderation\'2Fexamination. However\'2C the submission does not include information for Criterion 9. \line \line The Directorate recommends that the programme be accredited with a condition.\cell \pard 

